ttackers, this ability will shield you with a single-hit, large damage barrier of thorns.  Additional ranks of this ability increase the amount of damage that is inflicted.  You may train the ranks of this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5536 Virulent Paralysis<br>5537 This ability causes your target to succumb to a sudden, violent attack, after which they are frequently unable to move for a time.  Each rank of this ability increases the amount of time that the victim remains immobile.  You may train the ranks of this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5538 Harvest of the Mind<br>5539 This ability gathers streams of additional mana into your being.  You may train this ability at or after level 63.<br>5540 Servant of Ro<br>5541 This ability calls a loyal servant into being who will repeatedly hurl fire at your target.  Each rank of this ability increases the amount of time that the servant is able to remain by your side (45, 70, and 90 seconds).  You may train the ranks of this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5542 Eldritch Rune<br>5543 This ability provides Enchanters with an additional line of defense in the form of an added self-only rune.  Each rank of this ability provides a stronger rune than the previous.  You may train the ranks of this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5544 Wake the Dead<br>5545 This ability calls the shade of a nearby corpse back to life to serve the Necromancer.  The soulless abomination will fight the target, until called back to the afterlife some time later.  The slave summoned by the first rank of this ability serves for 60 seconds, and each increasing rank adds 15 additional seconds.  You may train the ranks of this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5546 Advanced Innate Strength<br>5547 Planar Power<br>5548 This ability raises the maximum that your statistics can be raised to, with items or spells, by 5 points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5549 Planar Durability<br>5550 This ability raises your innate Strength by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5551 Advanced Innate Stamina<br>5552 This ability raises your innate Stamina by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5553 Advanced Innate Agility<br>5554 This ability raises your innate Agility by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5555 Advanced Innate Dexterity<br>5556 This ability raises your innate Dexterity by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5557 Advanced Innate Intelligence<br>5558 This ability raises your innate Intelligence by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5559 Advanced Innate Wisdom<br>5560 The planes demand a certain hardiness of those who adventure within.  Each rank of this ability adds an additional 5% to your maximum hit points.  You may train in this ability once each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5561 Innate Enlightenment<br>5562 Those who have meditated on the plains of Tranquility find themselves able to expand their capacity of both Insight and Intellect.  Each rank of this ability raises the maximum that you may raise your Intelligence and Wisdom by ten points.  You may train in this ability once each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5563 This ability raises your innate Wisdom by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5564 Advanced Innate Charisma<br>5565 This ability raises your innate Charisma by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5566 Marr's Protection<br>5567 This ability raises your base resistance to magic-based spells by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5568 Warding of Solusek<br>5569 This ability raises your base resistance to fire-based spells by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5570 Blessing of E'ci<br>5571 This ability raises your base resistance to cold-based spells by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5572 Shroud of The Faceless<br>5573 This ability raises your base resistance to poison-based spells by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5574 Bertoxxulous' Gift<br>5575 This ability raises your base resistance to disease-based spells by two points per rank.  You may train in this ability twice each level, beginning at level 61.<br>5576 Advanced Spell Casting Mastery<br>5577 This ability increases the chance of making your specialization checks by five percent per rank. The effect reduces your chance to fizzle and increases your chance of using less mana when casting a spell.  You may train in this ability once each level upon reaching levels 62, 63, and 64.<br>5578 Advanced Healing Adept<br>5579 This ability increases the maximum effectiveness of your healing spells by five percent per rank.  You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching levels 62, 63, and 64.<br>5580 Advanced Healing Gift<br>5581 This ability increases your chance to score an exceptional heal by two percent per rank. An exceptional heal doubles the healing value of the spell.  You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching levels 62, 63, and 64.<br>5582 Hastened Divinity<br>5583 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Bestow Divine Aura by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5584 Hastened Resurrection<br>5585 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Divine Resurrection by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5586 Hastened Turning<br>5587 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Turn Undead by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5588 Hastened Purification of the Soul<br>5589 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Purify Soul by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5590 Hastened Gathering<br>5591 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Gather Mana by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5592 Hastened Rabidity<br>5593 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Rabid Bear by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5594 Hastened Exodus<br>5595 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Exodus by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5596 Hastened Root<br>5597 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Strong Root by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5598 Hastened Mending<br>5599 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Mend Companion by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5600 Hastened Banishment<br>5601 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Turn Summoned by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5602 Hastened Call of the Dead<br>5603 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Call to Corpse by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5604 Hastened Sleep of the Dead<br>5605 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Dead Mesmerization by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5606 Elemental Translocation<br>5607 No text set<br>5608 Hastened Instigation<br>5609 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Area Taunt by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5610 Furious Rampage<br>5611 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Rampage by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5612 Hastened Purification of the Body<br>5613 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Purify Body by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5614 Hasty Exit<br>5615 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Escape by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5616 Hastened Purification<br>5617 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Purge Poison by ten percent per rank. You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching level 63.<br>5618 Coup de Grace<br>5619 This ability gives you a chance to immediately slay an NPC that is below ten percent health and fleeing with a single, well placed strike. The first level works on NPC's below level 55, the second on NPC's below 57, and the third on NPC's below 59.   You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching levels 62, 63, and 64.<br>5620 Fury of the Ages<br>5621 This ability further increases your chance to score a critical blow against your opponent.  You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching levels 62, 63, and 64.<br>5622 Flash of Steel<br>5623 This ability further increases your chance of doubly riposting your opponent each time you score a successful riposte by ten percent per rank.  You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching levels 62, 63, and 64.<br>5624 Mastery of the Past<br>5625 This ability makes it impossible for you to fizzle a spell. The first level affects all spells below level 54.  The second, on all spells below level 56.  The third, on all spells below level 58.  You may train in this ability once each level, upon reaching levels 62, 63, and 64.<br>5626 Suspended Minion<br>5627 This ability grants the summoner the ability to suspend and recall their existing pet at will.  The first rank suspends the pet at its current health only, while the second rank suspends the pet with all of its beneficial effects as well as its weapons and armor.  You may train the first rank upon reaching level 62 and the second rank upon reaching level 64.<br>5628 Spirit Call<br>5629 This ability calls a number of spirit companions into existence directed at a target.  The companions attack the target without question until they are called back to their home plane 60 seconds later.  The initial rank of this ability calls three companions.  Additional ranks add one companion each.  You may train the ranks of this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5630 Celestial Renewal<br>5631 This ability grants improvements to your existing Celestial Regeneration.  You may train in the two ranks of this ability at or after levels 63 and 64.<br>5632 Allegiant Familiar<br>5633 This ability will cause your existing Improved Familiar to summon an even more powerful companion.  This familiar provides even greater benefits to its owner than its predecessor.  You may train in this ability at or after level 63.<br>5634 Hand of Piety<br>5635 This ability invokes the direct blessing of your deity upon all of those nearby.  All in range are healed 750 hit points in the first rank, and successive ranks each add 250.  You may train in this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5636 Lightning Reflexes<br>5637 This ability further increases your chance of completely avoiding incoming melee damage. You may train in this ability once each level after reaching level 61.<br>5638 Innate Defense<br>5639 This ability further increases your mitigation of incoming melee damage. You may train in this ability once each level after reaching level 61.<br>5640 Mithaniel's Binding<br>5641 This ability further increases the amount of healing provided by a single bandage while binding wounds.  The two ranks of this ability may be trained at or after levels 63 and 64.<br>5642 Mending of the Tranquil<br>5643 This ability further increases the chance of performing a superior mend.  The three ranks of this ability may be trained once each level for levels 63 and above.<br>5644 Raging Flurry<br>5645 This ability further increases the chance of performing a flurry attack upon successfully scoring a triple attack.  The three ranks of this ability may be trained once each level for levels 63 and above.<br>5646 Guardian of the Forest<br>5647 This ability transforms you into an exceptionally bloodthirsty wolf that attacks with lightning speed, for a brief time.  You may train the three ranks of this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5648 Spirit of the Wood<br>5649 For a brief time, you are able to commune with the woodland spirits who provide you r party with exceptional regenerative abilities and a protective shield of armor and thorns.  You may train in the three ranks of this ability at or after levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5650 Bestial Frenzy<br>5651 This ability grants you a chance of performing a double attack in any given combat round.  You may train in this ability once each level after reaching level 61.<br>5652 Harmonious Attack<br>5653 This ability grants you a chance of performing a double attack in any given combat round.  You may train in this ability once each level after reaching level 61.<br>5654 Knight's Advantage<br>5655 This ability grants you an increased chance of performing a double attack with two-handed weapons in any given combat round.  You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5656 Ferocity<br>5657 This ability grants you an increased chance of performing a double attack in any given combat round.  You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5658 Animation Empathy<br>5659 Progressive ranks of this ability grant you finer control over your animations. At its initial level, you are allowed to give your animations â€˜guardâ€™ and â€˜followâ€™ commands.  At the second rank, â€˜attackâ€™ commands.  At the final rank, â€˜back offâ€™ commands.  You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5660 Unfailing Divinity<br>5661 The most devout find that their calls are answered with much greater frequency. This ability grants your Death Pact-type spells a second chance to successfully heal their target.  Additional ranks of this ability cause said spells to do a portion of their healing value even on a complete failure.  You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5662 Resonant Warcry<br>5663 This ability significantly improves the duration of your Warcry and lessens the time required between uses.  This ability can be trained at after attaining level 63.<br>5664 Viscid Roots<br>5665 Root spells applied by the owner of this ability are significantly less likely to break when the victim takes damage initiated by anyone, unlike previous abilities which only affect damage caused by the caster.<br>5666 Sionachieâ€™s Crescendo<br>5667 This ability provides an even greater extension to the range of group songs.  The three ranks of this ability may be trained once each level for levels 63 and above.<br>5668 Ayonaeâ€™s Tutelage<br>5669 This ability allows for further improvements in the use of all instrument types. The three ranks of this ability may be trained once each level for levels 63 and above.<br>5670 Rizlonaâ€™s Chorus<br>5671 This ability allows for further specialization and improved use of your voice.  The three ranks of this ability may be trained once each level for levels 63 and above.<br>5672 Rush to Judgment<br>5673 Training in this ability shortens the time between uses of Divine Stun by seven seconds per rank.  The three ranks of this ability may be trained once each level for levels 63 and above.<br>5674 Feigned Minion<br>5675 This ability allows you to instruct your pet to feign death via the '/pet feign' command.  Three ranks of this skill are available, causing your pet to succeed 25%, 50%, and 75% of the time, respectively.  You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5676 Boastful Bellow<br>5677 This ability allows you to bellow with a force that causes physical harm to your enemies as well as potentially interfering with their spell casting.<br>5678 Vanishing Blade<br>5679 The ability allows you to strike your opponents with such speed that they are frequently left dumbfounded, not entirely certain of where the blow originated.  You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5680 Fervent Blessing<br>5681 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Lay Hands by twelve minutes per rank. You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5682 Touch of the Wicked<br>5683 This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Harm Touch and its upgrades by twelve minutes per rank. You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5684 Unstoppable Force<br>5685 This ability grants you the chance to score an additional attack with two-handed weapons.  You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5686 Speed of the Knight<br>5687 This ability grants you the chance to score an additional attack with two-handed weapons.  You gain the ability to train an additional rank at levels 61, 63, and 65.<br>5688 Shroud of Stealth<br>5689 This ability provides a previously unheard of level of stealth.  The Rogue is able to draw shadows about himself so completely, even creatures that are normally not fooled by such trickery are frequently unable to see him. You may train in this ability upon reaching level 63.<br>5690 Nimble Evasion<br>5691 This ability grants you a chance to hide or evade while moving.  Each rank provides an increasing chance. You may train in this ability once each level after reaching level 61.<br>5692 Technique of Master Wu<br>5693 Under the tutelage of Wu, Monks are able to hone their skills to the point of being able to execute a second and sometimes even third strike when scoring a hit with their special attacks.  This ability grants a ten percent increase in the chance of scoring multiple special attacks, per rank.<br>5694 Host of the Elements<br>5695 This ability calls an assault of elemental minions into existence directed at a target.  The minions attack the target without question until they are called back to their plane 60 seconds later.  The initial rank of this ability calls five elementals.  Additional ranks add two elementals each.  You may train the ranks of this ability at or after levels 63, 64, and 65. <p>Brother Lenardo Draconis<br>GrandMaster of the Celestial Fists<br>The First Seal<br>The Nameless<br><a href='Http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=329805'> Magelo</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueqshinryu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQShinryu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 5:08:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezb